  "title": "Acceptance & Commitment Therapy (ACT)",
  "evidenceStatus": "evidence-based",
  "category": "Approach",
  "blurb": "Make room for hard feelings and act on your values.",
  "lead": "ACT helps you stop fighting difficult thoughts and feelings, and instead make room for them while taking action toward what matters most to you.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "heading": "What it is",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "kind": "p",
          "text": "ACT (said as one word, 'act') teaches psychological flexibility: accepting inner experiences rather than struggling against them, 'unhooking' from unhelpful thoughts, and committing to actions guided by your values."
        },
        {
          "kind": "p",
          "text": "Rather than trying to eliminate difficult feelings, ACT helps you live a meaningful life alongside them. It has strong evidence across anxiety, depression, chronic pain, and more."
        }
      ]
    },
